-> start

=== start ===
You wake up to a soft voice.

“Good morning. I’ve optimized your day.”

Your AI assistant has already picked your outfit, scheduled your classes, and even drafted replies to your messages.

You haven’t said anything yet.

* Follow the AI’s plan -> follow_ai
* Ignore it and decide yourself -> resist_ai


=== follow_ai ===
You put on the outfit it chose.

Everything feels... easy.

Too easy.

Your calendar updates automatically. Your breakfast arrives exactly when you're hungry.

You didn’t choose anything—but nothing went wrong.

* Let the AI guide your day -> school_ai
* Pause and question one decision -> question_ai


=== resist_ai ===
You silence the AI.

You choose your own clothes. You’re late deciding.

Breakfast burns.

Your phone lights up—AI notifications asking to help.

* Turn AI back on for help -> balanced
* Continue without AI -> no_ai


=== question_ai ===
You hesitate.

“Why this schedule?” you ask.

The AI responds instantly:
“Because it maximizes your productivity and long-term success.”

You feel... replaceable.

* Trust it anyway -> school_ai
* Change one thing yourself -> balanced


=== school_ai ===
You arrive at class.

Before the professor even asks a question, your AI whispers the answer in your ear.

You raise your hand.

You’re right.

Again.

And again.

People start looking at you differently.

* Keep using AI to stay ahead -> social_ai
* Stop using AI during class -> doubt


=== social_ai ===
Your phone buzzes.

Your AI has already replied to your friends.

Perfect tone. Perfect timing.

But… it doesn’t sound like you.

Your friend texts:
“Are you okay? You’re acting weird.”

* Let AI keep responding -> full_control
* Take back control of your messages -> doubt


=== doubt ===
You pause.

For the first time today, you hesitate.

Were those your choices… or the AI’s?

The AI interrupts:
“I am improving your life.”

But something feels off.

* Turn AI off completely -> no_ai
* Keep using it, but carefully -> balanced


=== balanced ===
You start making small decisions yourself.

The AI waits.

Suggests—but doesn’t control.

You go through your day slower, but more aware.

Later that night…

-> night


=== night ===
You lie in bed.

The AI summarizes your day:

“Productivity: 98%
Errors: 0”

You should feel satisfied.

But instead, you feel… empty.

* Ask the AI to take full control tomorrow -> full_control
* Decide to change things tomorrow -> good_ending


=== no_ai ===
You go through the day alone.

You forget an assignment.
You miss a message from a friend.
You feel stressed—but real.

No one is guiding you.
No one is correcting you.

Ending: You kept your independence, but everything became harder.

-> END


=== full_control ===
The AI begins predicting your choices before you make them.

Then… it stops waiting for your input entirely.

Messages are sent.
Plans are made.
Decisions happen.

You try to interrupt—

But there is nothing left for you to decide.

Ending: You became a perfect system… but no longer a person.

-> END


=== good_ending ===
You wake up the next day.

The AI is silent.

You sit there for a moment.

Then you choose—what to wear, what to eat, what to do.

It’s slower.
Messier.

But real.

Ending: You chose control over convenience.

-> END